            "id": "PRRC_kwDOS97bAM7QWjwO",
            "body": "**<sub><sub>![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Decouple staged updates from HTTP ApiError**\n\nThe repo `AGENTS.md` asks domain code to stay independent of delivery mechanisms, but this new domain module returns `ApiError`; checked `api/src/error.rs`, and `ApiError` is backed by Axum `StatusCode`/`IntoResponse`, so the staged-push rules now remain coupled to HTTP semantics when reused from non-HTTP paths. The new boundary test also won't catch this because it forbids `crate::git`, `crate::http`, etc. but not `crate::error`.\n\nUseful? React with \ud83d\udc4d\u00a0/ \ud83d\udc4e.",
