            "body": "**<sub><sub>![P3 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P3-lightgrey?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Catch direct outer-layer references**\n\nBecause this only iterates over `use_statements(source)`, the boundary test ignores fully-qualified calls such as `crate::git::import::apply_receive_pack_update(...)` inside function bodies, which is the same dependency shape this refactor removed. In that case `domain_modules_do_not_import_outer_layers` would pass while domain code still depends on `git`/`state`; please scan the source for forbidden paths after stripping comments/strings or add a fixture for direct references.\n\nUseful? React with \ud83d\udc4d\u00a0/ \ud83d\udc4e.",
